    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Illustrations created specifically to illuminate some aspect of scientific inquiry, often in the field of biology. These may include unrealistic renderings, such as transparency, layering, etc.of subject matter that serve to illustrate functions or chronological events more clearly.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>為了闡明科學研究的某些面向而特別製作的插圖，常見於生物學領域，其表現內容可能包括非實體性呈現，例如題材的透明度、層次分布等，以更清楚說明功能特質或事件發生的時間順序。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Illustraties die speciaal zijn gemaakt om een bepaald aspect van wetenschappelijk onderzoek te belichten, vaak op het gebied van de biologie. Dit kunnen onrealistische weergaven zijn, zoals transparantie, gelaagdheid, enz. van onderwerpen die dienen om functies of chronologische gebeurtenissen duidelijker te illustreren.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000202/RKD</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
